text: What does a dorbsy look like?
Well, it's hard to tell for sure from the information provided. The flat insect with wings and ten little legs is almost always a dorbsy, but so are a few other creatures
Sometimes fish are also dorbsy, and sometimes birds with short legs are dorbsy, but not always
There is no clear way to differentiate those
Any shared characteristics that you could see?
They were, but it did not appear to be based on color reliably. I will say that birds with purple plumage tended to be dorbsy
Fish were in all colors and fin colors
Sometimes birds even with long legs were bordby if they had purple plumage
Birds with short legs tended to be dorbsy, but did not always have purple plumage
The flat bugs were dorbsy pretty much no matter what color they were
okay, that's really good to know.  did they always have 10 legs?  the flat bug ones?
Alright, I think that's really good information.  Thank you very much.
Anything else you can think of before we start?
You're welcome. That's all I can think of. Good luck :)
